COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) — Rangers at South Carolina state parks are kicking off 2022 by leading hikes across the state on New Year’s Day.The First Day Hike program has walks ranging from half a mile (800 meters) to 5 miles (8 kilometers) all throughout the day varying from leisurely strolls to strenuous workouts.The hikes include looking at wildflowers at Oconee Station State Park, hunting for shells and fossils during low tide at Edisto Beach State Park or learning about Revolutionary War history at the Battle of Musgrove Mill State Historic Site.The full schedule of hikes is at the South Carolina State Parks website.